en_627195_0	Sri Lanka Army Medical Corps (SLAMC) - trained twenty five Army Public Health Inspectors (PHIs) batch passed out on Wednesday (10) at the Colombo Army Hospital auditorium in Narahenpita.
en_627195_1	The SLAMC in close consultation with the Commander of the Army began this training since the scarcity of PHIs across the country affects inspection routines inside island-wide Army establishments which would pose a health hazard in the long run.
en_627195_2	Major General Sanjeewa Munasinghe, Director General Army Health Services & Colonel Commandant, SLAMC as the Chief Guest attended the ceremony and awarded certificates.
